Just before He bent His footsteps to the garden, Jesus had said to the disciples, “All ye shall be offended because of Me this night.” They had given Him the strongest assurance that they would go with Him to prison and to death. And poor, self-sufficient Peter had added, “Although all shall be offended, yet will not I.” Mark 14:27, 29.  The Desire of Ages, pp. 686-688.57 {CSA 32.10} 
Addressing Peter, Jesus said, “Simon, sleepest thou? couldest not thou watch one hour? {CSA 32.11} 
33
Watch ye and pray, lest ye enter into temptation. The spirit truly is ready, but the flesh is weak.” . . .
